<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ900626-0110</DOCNO><DOCID>900626-0110.</DOCID><HL>   Tandy Shareholder Rights Plan</HL><DATE>06/26/90</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE A4</SO><CO>   TAN</CO><LP>   FORT WORTH, Texas -- Tandy Corp. said its board approvedamendments to the company's shareholder rights plan thatwould allow individual holders to purchase additional sharesat a reduced price if an individual investor accumulates 15%of the company's stock.   Previously, the plan could be triggered if an investoracquired a 25% or greater stake without board approval. Theelectronics retailer and manufacturer said the changesweren't adopted in response to any specific effort to acquirecontrol of the company.</LP><TEXT/></DOC>